setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1N
*/
predeal south HA
predeal east  HKQ

dealer south

# South opens 1NT — balanced 15-17
sShape = shape(south, any 4333 + any 4432 + any 5332)
sHcp   = hcp(south) > 14 and hcp(south) < 18
southHand = sShape and sHcp

# North 10-12 raises to 3NT
nHcp = hcp(north) > 9 and hcp(north) < 13
northHand = nHcp

# East has the long heart threat
eHearts = hearts(east) > 4
eHcp    = hcp(east) < 11
eastHand = eHearts and eHcp

southHand and northHand and eastHand

action printoneline,
average "East heart length "       hearts(east),
average "West heart length "       hearts(west),
average "South HCP         "       hcp(south),
average "North HCP         "       hcp(north),
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Hold-Up at 3NT,\n\
--- Hold-Up at 3NT (duck twice in the opponents' long suit)\n\
South opens 1NT (15-17 balanced)，North raises to 3NT.\n\
\n\
Teaching feature: declarer has exactly ONE stopper in hearts (the Ace).\n\
East has a 5-card heart suit headed by KQ. West has 2-3 small hearts.\n\
\n\
If declarer wins the first heart，when East later gets the lead，East has\n\
4 more hearts to cash and 3NT goes down 1+.\n\
\n\
The hold-up technique: refuse to win the first or second heart trick. Win\n\
the third round only. By then，West (who started with 2-3 hearts) is OUT of\n\
hearts. Now you can lose the lead to West safely — West has no hearts to\n\
return.\n\
\n\
Things to think about:\n\
• How many times should you duck? Just enough to exhaust West's hearts.\n\
• After ducking，where will you take your remaining tricks?\n\
• Avoid losing the lead to East — they have the cashable winners.\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.bridgebum.com/hold-up_play.php\n\
%HoldUp3N%
